comments.text:
+locutus94 Not being good at compromise means you can't have pretty much 
any long term relationship. It's unhealthy to be so wrapped up in your own 
desires and not consider the wants and needs of others. 

Also, if you communicate, you won't fight half as much. Bickering over 
things like this video is fine so long as you move past it quickly, 
fighting is not a normal part of a relationship nor is resentment after 
getting to completely know someone, if you resent them in the end, then 
there were things left unsaid that should of been discussed or you didn't 
know the real them before jumping into their lives completely. But people 
are both too stubborn or too embarrassed to get that close to someone and 
say how they feel if they're jealous, sad or upset. It's something everyone 
should work on. Even if it's over something stupid, an adjusted person can 
get past it, and understand that we all get mad at stupid things and that's 
ok.

For the record, I don't believe in the one. My boyfriend and I know there 
is someone who may fit us better. Relationships are about working on 
becoming the best person you can be and vice versa for your partner. You 
find someone who shares similar interests, thought patterns and even with 
the differences is willing to discuss it like adults or respect your 
opinion if there are no facts to back either side up. There is ALWAYS 
someone better out there. There is no perfect person. The person will 
become perfect to you through hard work and communication. But you do have 
to find someone you click well with and whose particular idiosyncrasies 
don't drive you up the wall, or maybe the person is willing to work on 
them. Give and take is the name of that game so to speak.
